{{Infobox planet | minorplanet= yes | background= #D6D6D6 | name= 780 Armenia | mpc_name= (780) Armenia | alt_names= 1914 UC | discoverer= [[G. N. Neujmin]] | discovered= 25 January 1914 | discovery_site= [[Simeiz Observatory]] | epoch= 31 July 2016 ([[Julian day|JD]] 2457600.5) | orbit_ref= <ref name="JPL"/> | eccentricity= 0.097135 | semimajor= {{Convert|3.1144|AU|Gm|abbr=on}} | perihelion= {{Convert|2.8119|AU|Gm|abbr=on}} | aphelion= {{Convert|3.4169|AU|Gm|abbr=on|lk=on}} | period= 5.50 [[Julian year (astronomy)|yr]] (2007.5 [[Julian year (astronomy)|d]]) | inclination= 19.085° | asc_node= 144.857° | arg_peri= 214.403° | mean_anomaly= 346.438[[Degree (angle)|°]] | mean_motion= {{Deg2DMS|0.17932|sup=ms}} / day | observation_arc= 107.14 yr (39134 d) | uncertainty= 0 | abs_magnitude= 9.00 | rotation= {{Convert|19.891|h|d|abbr=on|lk=on}} | albedo= {{val|0.0498|0.002}} | mean_radius= {{val|47.20|0.85}} [[Kilometre|km]] }}
'''780 Armenia''' is a [[minor planet]] in the [[asteroid belt]] orbiting the [[Sun]]. It is named after the [[Kingdom of Armenia (disambiguation)|Kingdom of Armenia]], now [[Armenia]].
This object is the namesake of the [[Armenia family]], a very small [[Asteroid family|family]] of 13–76 asteroids that share similar spectral properties and [[orbital elements]]; hence they may have arisen from the same collisional event. All members have a relatively high [[orbital inclination]].<ref name="Novakovic2011"/>
